The '''Sustainability Network'''  ({{lang-pt|Rede Sustentabilidade}}) (REDE) is a [[Brazilian politics|Brazilian political party]]<ref name="TSE"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Seja mais um elo da Rede Sustentabilidade!|url=http://www.redesustentabilidade.org.br|website=www.redesustentabilidade.org.br|language=Portuguese}}</ref> founded in 2013 by [[Marina Silva]], Brazilian politician from [[Acre, Brazil|Acre]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Brazil's Marina Silva launches 'sustainability party'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-21487993|accessdate=15 July 2016|publisher=BBC}}</ref>

The party formed a strategic alliance with the [[Brazilian Socialist Party]] for the [[Brazilian general election, 2014|2014 Brazilian general election]], until its registration as an independent political party was approved in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2015/09/tse-registra-rede-sustentabilidade-partido-fundado-por-marina-silva.html|title=TSE registra Rede Sustentabilidade, partido fundado por Marina Silva|date=22 September 2015|publisher=}}</ref>

The Sustainability Network has 19,090 members as of January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inter04.tse.jus.br/ords/dwtse/f?p=2001:104:::NO:::|title=Eleitores filiados|website=inter04.tse.jus.br}}</ref>

For the [[Brazilian general election, 2018|Brazilian general election of 2018]] REDE has formed with the [[Green Party (Brazil)|Green Party]] the coalition ''United to transform Brazil'', in support of Marina Silva.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.valor.com.br/politica/5711971/rede-aprova-por-aclamacao-chapa-marina-silva-eduardo-jorge|title=Rede aprova por aclamação chapa Marina Silva-Eduardo Jorge|date=4 August 2018|access-date=8 September 2018|publisher=Valor Econômico|first=Marcelo|last=Ribeiro|first2=Isadora|last2=Peron|language=portuguese}}</ref>

